Positive sentiment for Similac has been at an average of 51% in the last 3 months. Whereas negative sentiment averages at 5%.

Note: Sentiment usually take around 3 months to showcase a significant change. The high proportion of neutral comes from brand mentions without accompanying relevant text for analysis, as well as queries and information bits.

Over the last 3 months, Similac's emotions association has majorly been positive with Trust, Joy and Anticipation forming about 70% of the emotional analysis. Interestingly fear around the product has been eliminated and negative sentiment for Similac is no more dictated by it.
Note:  Emotions can be overlapping for a same set of conversations. I.E. A verbatim can be classified under both Trust and Joy.
